facts.value: John (Jonathan?) Benjamin Crist was born 25 March 1884 in North Hampton, Ohio to Nicholas and Sarah (Brubaker) Crist, their second child and older son. The Crist family moved from Ohio to Kansas before 1900. He married Eva Lena Barnhart 18 January 1905 in Olathe, Kansas. John was a farmer. They had a son Ezra in 1906. The family moved to Washington by 1916 where John had a fruit farm There five more children were born. Two of them, Dartha and a baby boy, died as infants. The other children were Marie, Kenneth and Betty. By 1930 John worked as a housing building contractor. By 1954 John and Eva must have moved to the Los Angeles area where Eva died on June 8. On 14 August 1954, John married a widow, Vivian Marie Furray Pierce in San Fernando, California. John died in 1970 and was buried in Washington.
